TITLE: Eveline Rosina Henty Scholarships
INFO: STATUS: Closed | VALUE: $4,000.00

[Overview]
The late Eveline Rosina Glyde donated funds to The University of Western Australia (the University) to assist and encourage Indigenous Australian and Torres Strait Islander students to pursue a bridging course or an undergraduate degree course at the university.

[Eligibility]
To be eligible to apply for the scholarship, an applicant must—
(a) be a domestic student;
(b) an Australian Indigenous or Torres Strait Islander;
(c) experiencing financial hardship;
(d) be a commencing student;
(e) be enrolled, or eligible to enrol—
(i) full-time unless the selection body is satisfied that there are exceptional circumstances5 which preclude full-time enrolment; and
(ii) in an orientation/bridging course offered by the School of Indigenous Studies or;
(iii) in an undergraduate degree course

[Benefits]
To enable Australian Indigenous and Torres Strait Islander students to pursue either a bridging course or an undergraduate degree course at the university.

TITLE: OMNI EXECUTIVE INDIGENOUS LEADERS SCHOLARSHIP
INFO: STATUS: Closed | VALUE: $30,000.00

[Overview]
Omni Executive has donated funds to The University of Western Australia ('the University') to provide a scholarship to encourage and assist high achieving Indigenous Australian students to commence and pursue an eligible undergraduate qualification at the University.

[Eligibility]
To be eligible to apply for the scholarship, an applicant must—
(a) be a domestic student;
(b) an Australian indigenous person;
(c) be a commencing student;
(d) be enrolled, or eligible to enrol—
(i) full-time unless the selection body is satisfied that there are exceptional circumstances which preclude full-time enrolment; and
(ii) in an eligible course listed in 8.2.
2. Eligible courses include—
(a) Bachelor of Science;
(b) Bachelor of Engineering, majoring in—
(i) Automation and Robotics;
(ii) Civil Engineering;
(iii) Electrical and Electronic Engineering;
(iv) Mechanical Engineering; or
(v) Software Engineering;
(c) Bachelor of Philosophy, Politics and Economics;
(d) Bachelor of Advanced Computer Science; or
(e) an undergraduate degree course with a major in—
(i) Computer Science;
(ii) Computing and Data Science;
(iii) Data Science;
(iv) Political science; or
(v) Political Science and International Relations.

[Benefits]
To encourage and assist high achieving Indigenous Australian students to commence and pursue an eligible undergraduate qualification at the University.

TITLE: UWA Sport - Sports Excellence Scholarship
INFO: STATUS: Closed | VALUE: $15,000.00

[Overview]
The University of Western Australia ('the University') provides scholarships to assist and encourage high-performing student-athletes to pursue an undergraduate qualification at the University and realise their dual career focus.

[Eligibility]
To be eligible to apply for the scholarship, an applicant must—
(a) be a domestic student;
(b) be a commencing student (or have at least three years of study remaining at their current study rate);
(c) qualify for the UWA Student Athlete Development Program (SADP) as an elite or emerging tier athlete; and
(d) be enrolled, or eligible to enrol in an undergraduate degree course at the University.

An Elite athlete is classed a—
• Open Age World Championships team;
• Olympic/Commonwealth Games/World Cup Team;
• World University Games;
• Starting line-up of a professional team;
• World University Championships;
• Senior International Representation.

An Emerging athlete is classed a—
• State Team Representation at the open level (providing the nominated sport has no professional league);
• WAIS squad member/scholarship holder;
• National underage team member;
• National League team player/professional club player squad member.

Applicants need to provide a letter of support from their relevant sporting body (or sporting organisation if not able to be obtained by the sporting body). The letter must confirm current representation level as well as highlight any recent sporting achievements achieved.

[Benefits]
To assist and encourage high-performing student-athletes to pursue an undergraduate qualification at the University and realise their dual career focus.
